# Copy this file to ".env" (with the dot at the start, no .example) — or just
# add your key through the in-app welcome screen, which writes it here for you.
# The .env file is YOURS and stays on your computer — it never goes to GitHub.

# ElevenLabs API key — the only key this Node needs.
# Get one at https://elevenlabs.io  →  Profile  →  API Keys.
# Voice cloning needs a paid plan (Starter tier or above).
#
# A key set here is imported once, on first run, as the "built-in" shared key.
# After that, manage keys in the app (top-right "API keys") — they're stored in
# a private, git-ignored file (elevenlabs-keys.json), not in this file.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# Optional — newsroom display name shown in the GROUNDED top bar and on the
# cohort dashboard. Defaults to "Explain".
# NEWSROOM=

# Optional — change if you want the app on a different port.
# PORT=3000
